This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes an improvement to a popular differentiable neural architecture search algorithm. It also involves experiments on CIFAR and ImageNet datasets, which are commonly used in machine learning research. 

It could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as the experiments involve image classification tasks. 

Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as neural architecture search is a subfield of AI research. 

cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a possible sub-category as the paper involves optimizing neural network architectures. 

Finally, it could be categorized under cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) as the paper involves searching for optimal neural network architectures, which could have implications for hardware design.
